article.headline: Massachusetts 35, Delaware 7
article.story:
NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Liam Coen completed 21-of-26 passes for 318
yards and a touchdown to lead Massachusetts to a 35-7 win over
Delaware on Saturday.

Steve Baylark rushed for 109 yards and a touchdown for the
Minutemen (7-2, 6-1 Atlantic 10), who beat Delaware by their
largest-ever margin. The Blue Hens have dominated the series, 22-5.

It was the worst home loss for Delaware (4-5, 1-5) since 1986.

Leading 21-0 at halftime, Massachusetts made it 28-0 when Cohen
hit Racheed Rancher for an 84-yard touchdown, the second-longest TD
pass in school history.

Massachusetts finished with 496 yards of total offense while
holding Delaware to 305 yards. The Minutemen held a nine-minute
advantage in time of possession.

After the opening kickoff, Massachusetts marched 81 yards in 17
plays, capped off by Coen's 3-yard touchdown run.

Baylark made it 14-0 late in the second quarter with a 1-yard
run that concluded an 11-play, 76-yard drive. The Minutemen scored
again just 20 seconds later, when Tracy Belton returned an
interception 45 yards for a touchdown with 30 seconds remaining in
the first half.

The Minutemen had four interceptions in the game. Sonny Riccio,
who had only been intercepted twice this season, threw three picks.

Riccio went 12-of-23 for 95 yards, including a 20-yard touchdown
pass to Armand Cauthen in the third quarter. Omar Cuff had 95 yards
rushing for the Blue Hens.
